You leave your home after you have
reached adulthood. Wanting to know
what kind of man your father was.
Your father left you a note and a
string of clues.
"If you really want to meet me. aim
for the stars"
You were raised in a city as an
orphan. And you mysteriously got a
note after your 20th.
The galaxy knows of your father in a
great regard. Albeit. He is a bit kooky.
He is known for countless
innovations. Most notable being
- Space travel
- Tooth paste
- Food delivery using asteroids.
GAMEPLAY #1
You move between planets and nodes
ACTIONS
Talk to
Mechanic
CAPTAINS LOG
You go to a planet.
You try to go to different places and try to
talk with locals or interact with stuff.
Some locals will point you to areas and
then you unlock those areas and see them on the map.
YOU
- A quiet young adult, who has longed for
family.
-You were taken in by a family who gives
you your fathers letter at your 20th
- You are a bit angry and upset at your
wizard father
- You inherited some of his quirkiness
- You long for friends, but it's hard to
make friends.
- You have an innovator's heart.
FATHER
- An embellishment of brilliance but also
an isolated genius
- Ran away from his family not too long
after his son was born
- Wants to reconnect, but scared.
- Tries to talk to his son in very indirect
ways
- Alot of his inventions were ideas of
what his son could be.
GAMEPLAY #2
Game is more story based.
There will be a direct through line.
